    "recap_headline": "Baseball",
    "recap_text": "LOS ANGELES\n\u2013 The No. 13 USC baseball team rode an early lead to a 7-2 victory over Washington on Saturday night at Dedeaux Field.\nThe Trojans scored all seven runs in the first two innings, moving to 23-1 overall and 7-1 in Big Ten play with the win. Washington falls to 9-13, 4-4.\nThe Trojan bats exploded out of the gates with three runs in the first and four in the second to take a commanding early lead.\nAugie Lopez\ncapped the three-run first with a solo-homer and\nKevin Takeuchi\ndrove in his second run of the game with an RBI double to cap the second, after also sacrificing a run home in the first.\nAdrian Lopez\n,\nIsaac Cadena\nand\nAbbrie Covarrubias\neach had RBI in the first two innings as well.\nWashington hit a solo-homer in the second to score their first run of the game, but wouldn't get another off of\nGrant Govel\nuntil his final inning on the mound in the sixth, with the Huskies scoring their second on an RBI single. Govel limited the damage each time, giving up just the two runs on four hits and one walk. He stranded three Washington runners on the night.\nAfter\nSax Matson\ntossed a scoreless seventh inning,\nDiego Velazquez\nbrought it home with two scoreless frames on the mound, recording his second strikeout on the final batter of the game.\nTOP PERFORMERS\nGrant Govel\n: W, 6.0 IP, 4H, 2R, BB, 6K\nDiego Velazquez\n: 2.0 IP, 2H, 0R, 0BB, 2K\nIsaac Cadena\n: 2-for-4, RBI, R, 2B\nKevin Takeuchi\n: 1-for-3, 2 RBI, 2B, SF\nCOMING UP\nThe Trojans and Huskies wrap things up on Sunday at 1 p.m. on B1G+. USC then hosts No. 17 Oregon State on Tuesday before heading to Maryland next weekend.\nHear from Head Coach\nAndy Stankiewicz\n(\n@turntwo17\n) after his ball club moved to 23-1 with another victory over Washington \u270c\ufe0f\n#FightOn\nx\n@YETICoolers\npic.twitter.com/sSeBreI1Vk\n\u2014 USC Baseball (@USC_Baseball)\nMarch 22, 2026",
